@ApiAudience.Framework
@ApiStability.Experimental
public final class ReferenceCountedCache<K,V extends Closeable>
extends Object
implements Closeable

A keyed cache which keeps track of how many outstanding users of the cached instance exist. When the reference count falls to 0, the cached object (which must implement Closeable), is removed from the cache and closed. Clients of ReferenceCountedCache *must* have a corresponding #release(K) call for every #get(K) after the cached object will no longer be used. After the #release(K) call, the cached object must no longer be used. The ReferenceCountedCache may optionally be closed, which will preemptively close all cached entries regardless of reference count. See the javadoc of close() for caveats.

Method Detail

create

public static <K,V extends Closeable> ReferenceCountedCache<K,V> create(com.google.common.base.Function<K,V> cacheLoader)
Create a ReferenceCountedCache using the supplied function to create cached values on demand. The function may be evaluated with the same key multiple times in the case that the key becomes invalidated due to the reference count falling to 0. A function need not handle the case of a null key, but it should never return a null value for any key.

Type Parameters:
K - key type of cache.
V - value type (must implement Closeable) of cache.
Parameters:
cacheLoader - function to compute cached values on demand. Should never return null.
Returns:
a new ReferenceCountedCache.

public void release(K key)

Indicate to the cache that the client is done using the cached value for the given key. Clients of ReferenceCountedCache must call this after finishing using the value retrieved from the cache. The retrieved is no longer guaraunteed to be valid after it is released back to the ReferenceCountedCache

close

public void close()
           throws IOException
Make a best effort at closing all the cached values. This method is *not* guaranteed to close every cached value if there are concurrent users of the cache. As a result, this method should only be relied upon if only a single thread is using this cache while #close is called.

Specified by:
close in interface Closeable
Throws:
IOException - if any entry throws an IOException while closing. An entry throwing an IOException will prevent any further entries from being cleaned up.
